Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and slice the @potatoes{2} into ½ cm thick rounds.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the garlic for ~{1%minute}. Add 125ml water (double for 4p), 
@beef stock{1%sachet} and @creme fraiche{125%grams}.

Carefully add the potatoes to the sauce. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and 
@pepper{to taste} (double both for 4p).

Bring to the boil, cover and reduce heat to medium. Stir regularly to prevent 
sticking.

Simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}, until potatoes are parboiled then add the 
@truffle oil{2%packets} and stir to incorporate.

Carefully transfer the parboiled potatoes and truffle sauce to an 
appropriately-sized #oven dish{}.

Pop into the oven and bake until the sauce is bubbling and the potatoes are 
cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: You want the dauphinoise to be 2-3 cm thick—keep this in mind when 
> choosing an oven dish.

Meanwhile, place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. 
Season the @21 Day Aged Irish Sirloin Steak{250%grams} with @salt{to taste} and 
@pepper{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the sirloin until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for 
medium-rare. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its 
> packaging.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it more well-done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover and allow to rest. Meat is safe to 
eat when the outside is browned.

Meanwhile, cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large 
florets.

Wipe the pan before returning it to medium-high heat with a drizzle of 
@oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the broccoli for ~{2-3%minutes} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and 
@pepper{to taste}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} then cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. 
Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Thinly slice the sirloin and divide between plates.

Serve the truffled potato dauphinoise and broccoli alongside.